-- AT&T to strike deal with DirecTV in as soon as two weeks - WSJ
-- 
-- Mon May 12, 2014 04:45PM EDT
-- None



May 12 (Reuters) - AT&T Inc <T.N> is expected to strike a deal with DirecTV <DTV.O> in as early as two weeks, the Wall Street Journal reported on Monday, citing sources.

The mobile services provider and the satellite TV company are discussing a cash-and-stock deal, the sources told the Journal. (http://link.reuters.com/zuf39v) DirecTV is working with advisers including Goldman Sachs Group <GS.N> to evaluate a possible combination following a recent takeover approach, Reuters reported last week. [ID:nL2N0NT2CU] AT&T declined to comment, while DirecTV representatives were not immediately available for comment.